import time
import random
from vllm.core.evictor import LRUEvictor, EvictionPolicy, make_evictor


def bench(n_add=50000, n_update=50000, n_evict=25000, seed=42):
    rng = random.Random(seed)
    evictor = make_evictor(EvictionPolicy.LRU)

    # Generate blocks
    blocks = [
        (i, rng.getrandbits(32), rng.randint(1, 128), rng.random() * 1000.0)
        for i in range(n_add)
    ]

    t0 = time.perf_counter()
    for bid, ch, nht, ts in blocks:
        evictor.add(bid, ch, nht, ts)
    t_add = time.perf_counter() - t0

    # Perform updates on a subset
    upd_idx = [rng.randrange(n_add) for _ in range(n_update)]
    t1 = time.perf_counter()
    base = 1000.0
    for idx in upd_idx:
        bid, ch, nht, ts = blocks[idx]
        base += 1.0
        evictor.update(bid, base)
    t_upd = time.perf_counter() - t1

    # Evict some blocks
    t2 = time.perf_counter()
    acc = 0
    for _ in range(n_evict):
        bid, ch = evictor.evict()
        acc ^= (bid ^ ch)
    t_evict = time.perf_counter() - t2

    return t_add, t_upd, t_evict, acc


if __name__ == "__main__":

    p = argparse.ArgumentParser()
    p.add_argument("--n_add", type=int, default=50000)

    print(f"add={t_add:.4f}s update={t_upd:.4f}s evict={t_evict:.4f}s checksum={acc}")

import time
import random
from vllm.core.evictor import LRUEvictor, EvictionPolicy, make_evictor


def bench(n_add=50000, n_update=50000, n_evict=25000, seed=42):
    rng = random.Random(seed)
    evictor = make_evictor(EvictionPolicy.LRU)

    # Generate blocks
    blocks = [
        (i, rng.getrandbits(32), rng.randint(1, 128), rng.random() * 1000.0)
        for i in range(n_add)
    ]
